===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|byen}}, {{m|enm|biggen}}, {{m|enm|buggen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|bycġan||to buy, pay for, acquire, redeem, ransom, procure, get done, sell}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*bugjaną||to buy}}, of uncertain origin. Perhaps from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bhūgh-||to bend}}, or from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bheugh-||to take away, deliver}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{m|sco|by||to buy, purchase}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{m|osx|buggian}}, {{m|osx|buggean||to buy}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{m|non|byggja||to procure a wife, lend at interest, let out}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{m|got|𐌱𐌿𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽||to buy|sc=Goth}}.

